manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Anti-colic valve. The anti-colic valve in the nipple helps to reduce symptoms of colic by preventing excessive air from getting into your baby’s milk. Natural latch. Our bottle nipples are made from soft silicone and have a special breast-like shape that encourages a natural latch and prevents nipple confusion when switching between bottle and breast. Natural pace. The soft silicone nipple flexes and stretches like mom and allows your baby to feed comfortably at their own pace.

Most recommended baby bottle. Our Closer to Nature Anti-Colic bottles are #1 for easily switching between bottle and breast*. 100% leakproof. When the screw ring, nipple and cap are all secured, your baby bottle is completely mess-free and leakproof, even if it’s turned upside down or shaken. Easy clean and BPA free. These bottles are suitable for use in the dishwasher, microwave and sterilizers. All Tommee Tippee bottles are BPA- and phthalate-free for your ultimate reassurance.

Go with the flow. We offer different flow rates to keep up with your growing baby. Every baby is different but as a guide we suggest slow flow and vari flow for 0+months, medium flow for 3+ months and fast flow for 6+ months. Change me. Our nipples are silky soft. Change them if they get damaged or bitten by tiny teeth. Closer to Nature baby bottles are ONLY compatible with Closer to Nature nipples and cannot be used with Advanced Anti-Colic bottle nipples. Squeeze me. When assembling your baby bottle, hold the nipple up to the light to check the slit in the silicone isn’t sealed closed. If it has, pinch it gently between your fingers or with nipple tongs to re-open. If the valve has sealed closed, your bottle won’t vent properly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars We love Tommee Tippee but too fast.
reviews.reviewText: Tommee Tippee is amazing. I have never been disappointed with any of their bottles. They are high quality and last a really long time. I saved ones from my four year and they still all have the markings on them. These ones are perfect for the first few months where they don't take too much at a feeding. For EBF Moms this was the first bottle my daughter took from Daddy at two weeks old and we never looked back. For formula feeding moms this bottle is easy to fill and scoop because of the wide opening. The nipples are durable. The price is always great for a higher end bottle and you will not be disappointed. If something is wrong with the nipple either make sure it is only hand washed or make sure you a re pinching the valve first...otherwise it is probably defective. Also they sell these bottles everywhere so if you ever run out you will have no problem finding them.Edit: So after using these for 3 weeks with my newborn I can safely say I will not be using these for awhile Not sure why but these and the Avent Naturals are the only bottles that my baby consistently chokes on. They are slow flow so I'm not sure why but she does really well with the Dr. Browns the Playtex and The Nuk. Moral of the story, not every baby will take well to every bottle so don't buy tons of one brand like I did.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars GREAT, just watch those fingers!
reviews.reviewText: Since my daughter was born, we have tried numerous brands of bottles. We started off with the Nuk brand since they seemed to have great reviews. However, she absolutely drowned and choked every time she used it. We then got the slowest flow nipples by Nuk and it was still too much for her and caused her to still choke on her milk and have terrible gas pains. We went on to a few other brands with the same issue of choking or eating way too fast (under 3 minutes) which defeats the point of pacefeeding since I am also breastfeeding. So, we decided to use Tommee Tippee extra slow flow (0) and she no longer chokes or has gas pains. Now, keep in mind that it's called Slow Flow for a reason. My husband got impatient that each feeding takes her about 15-20 minutes, depending on how sleepy she is, but I'd take that over her discomfort any day. My biggest gripe about these bottles are the space in between the bottle cap and the bottle itself. Even when twisted tightly shut, there is a gap large enough for my 5-week-old to curl her fingertips into. I had a scare the other day when she managed to get the tip of her pinky stuck but luckily I noticed before I pulled the bottle away. I could've hurt her otherwise.Pros:- No more choking on milk- Prevents gas pain- Baby is comfortable and not fussy when eating- Easy to hold- Great for breastfeeding mamas who are pace feedingCons:- Gap large enough for baby's fingertips to slide into- A little difficult to clean with all the curvatures- Nipple sometimes gets clogged and needs to be squeezed in order to create a smooth flow again- Feedings take on average 17 minutes
